<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="370" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[828,1463,1516,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis box="[858,966,1690,1713]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="370">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[1086,1173,1688,1712]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1086,1173,1688,1712]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="370">Agelena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other Agelenini by having a prolateral bulge on the bulb (embolic base extending the tegulum), which is lacking in other genera.
</paragraph>
